  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine the accuracy of preoperative clinical examination
      in penetrating injuries
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Penetrating injuries is a common cause of severe neurovascular damage, both in adults and
      children.we evaluated the accuracy of the preoperative clinical examination in depicting
      lesions caused by penetrating wounds of hands or forearms.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
